<D>__{i just want some time to think. what's the rush? i will go next year.}
<C>__{steve}
<D>__{we'll talk later.}
<A>__{steve walks off toward laurie's edsel. laurie gets out. she's wearing a letterman's sweater with a large "class of '62" emblazoned on the shoulder. steve goes to her and they hug. on the radio, the music ends, and the wolfman's intro tune comes on.}
<C>__{radio}
<P>__{(singing)}
<D>__{"here comes the wolfman wolfman jack!"}
<C>__{wolfman }
<D>__{oh, we're gonna rock and roll ourselves to death baby. you got the wolfman jack show!}
<A>__{mel's drive in night as the radio blares "sixteen candles," we see that with the darkness burger city has come alive. a continual line of hot rods pulls into the parking lot to check out the parked cars, then returns to the maindrag. carhops glide by on roller skates. curt and john are fooling around in front of the deuce coupe. a horn honks and they turn as a '60 ford with three girls in it slows by them. a girl leans out the window and smiles.}
<C>__{girl}
<D>__{hi john!}
<A>__{the girls in the car all screech and giggle as they zoom off.}
